Task #52 (2.4 multiplayer): the BSD nonblocking-socket surface --
FIONBIO + FIONREAD + SO_BROADCAST, with nonblocking READS driven by
netd (E_AGAIN), not a pouch-side readiness poll.

TyrQuake's UDP driver (NQ/net_udp.c) died at UDP_OpenSocket:
socket(PF_INET, SOCK_DGRAM, IPPROTO_UDP) succeeded (0016 accepts the
explicit protocol 17) but ioctl(fd, FIONBIO, &1) -- the BSD idiom for
nonblocking mode -- had no pouch surface, returned -1, and the driver
closed the socket: "UDP_Init: Unable to open control socket, UDP
disabled". The game loop then needs nonblocking recvfrom (the /net data
read BLOCKS since net-6a-1).

THE DESIGN: a nonblocking read is TRY-AND-EAGAIN, never poll-then-read.
netd owns it -- a `nonblock` ctl verb puts a connection in nonblocking
mode, and an empty-but-open `data` read then answers E_AGAIN (Rlerror
11 -> the guest's EWOULDBLOCK via syscall_cp's __syscall_ret) instead
of parking a PendingRead. So the read path NEVER touches the readiness
bridge -- which matters: the poll-before-read design (an earlier cut of
this patch) submitted a readiness probe on EVERY read that the kernel
poll kthread then Tflush-abandoned, and the abandoned tags sat
`awaiting_flush` until netd Rflushed them; a tight nonblocking read loop
piled them up faster than the Rflush and EXHAUSTED the shared netd
session's 64-tag pool -> `alloc_tag<0` in p9_session_send_read ->
spurious EIO on every subsequent data read (root-caused with a kernel
branch tracer: the readiness path reused an already-parked op [its tag
held -> it kept working] while new synchronous data Treads could not
allocate a tag). netd-EAGAIN removes the churn at its source.

This patch (pouch side; 4 files):

  src/internal/_pouch_socket.h  The per-slot `nonblock` flag (set by
      FIONBIO; gates FIONREAD) + the pouch_sock_readable declaration
      (the FIONREAD-only readiness probe, documented COLD-path).

  src/network/_pouch_socket.c   pouch_sock_readable: one 0-timeout poll
      of the slot's poll target (net-6b ready sibling / the /srv byte
      stream), any nonzero revents == readable. ALSO: the slot-reuse
      reset list gains nonblock AND the pre-existing missing bulk_hint
      (a recycled slot inherited a stale bulk hint -> a later AF_UNIX
      bind spuriously posted DMSRVBULK; same-stroke fix).

  src/misc/ioctl.c              FIONBIO: set slot->nonblock + WRITE the
      netd `nonblock 1`/`nonblock 0` ctl verb (best-effort; a failed
      write degrades to blocking, never wrong). FIONREAD: the 1/0
      TRUTHINESS contract via pouch_sock_readable (the /net readiness
      surface reports ready/not-ready, never queue depth; TyrQuake
      net_udp.c:302 tests nonzero only). Both FAM_INET-only; any other
      fd -> ENOTTY (no kernel ioctl surface). The F_SETFL/O_NONBLOCK
      fcntl route stays a documented seam (no consumer).

  src/network/setsockopt.c      SO_BROADCAST joins the FAM_INET
      accept-as-noop allowlist (TyrQuake UDP_Broadcast must not error;
      an actual 255.255.255.255 send is a slirp dead end, which UDP
      tolerates -- the datagram vanishes).

The read/recv/recvfrom shims are UNCHANGED (pristine): the nonblocking
behavior is entirely netd-driven, so the tagged read already returns
EWOULDBLOCK naturally once the connection is nonblock. Nonblocking
WRITES are out of scope (the /net send path does not park the caller;
the UDP send_slice drops on a full tx ring -- no gate needed). The
recvfrom src-fill caveat (the recorded remote, not the per-datagram
sender) is inherited from net-6a-2 unchanged -- any-source datagrams
DO flow (netd discards the recv meta, no filter).

Companion: netd server.rs grows a per-connection `nonblock` flag (the
`nonblock` ctl verb) and returns E_AGAIN on an empty nonblock data read
(the FK_DATA WouldBlock arm); ninep.rs adds E_AGAIN = 11.

Proof: the pouch-hello-net #52 leg (FIONBIO round-trip, nonblocking
recvfrom EWOULDBLOCK when empty, a real datagram over netd's resident
127.0.0.1 loopback converging to a nonblocking read, FIONREAD idle 0,
SO_BROADCAST accepted) -- boot-fatal via the joey net-5 PROBE; plus the
live TyrQuake connect (the ls-gfx-mp leg).
